      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 824: 🔴 Critical Issues - The audio-triggered bitrate reduction calls setNewBitrate() but does not update the existing video bitrate backoff state such as lastBitrateDecrease / REMB decrease state. The normal RTCP adaptation loop can therefore raise the bitrate again on the next cycle and undo the audio-priority decision. Route this through the same decrease path used by video congestion handling, or update the same cooldown/decrease markers before applying the new bitrate.",
